{"word":"Παῦλος","slug":"Παῦλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Παῦλος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> Paulus] a Roman surname, <b>Paul<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> a proconsul Sergius Paulus <b><a href='B:510 13:7'>Ac 13:7</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Σέργιος\">Σέργιος</a></el>). <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> the apostle Paul <b><a href='B:510 13:9'>Ac 13:9</a></b> (and thereafter <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Ac); <b><a href='B:520 1:1'>Ro 1:1</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> in Paul’s letters; <b><a href='B:680 3:15'>2 Pt 3:15</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πατρῷος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:παύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}